title: Fork Yoke, Bottom
desc: FORK YOKE, BOTTOM, NOS, FOR NARROW FORKS USED ON 1967 B44R, C25 & B25 - CAN ALSO BE USED ON C15C FRAMED BIKES AND THE B44E AND B44EA MODELS - SEE BELOW.THIS BOTTOM CLAMP IS IDENTICAL TO 40-5111 EXCEPT THE TWO POSTS THAT STAND UP OFF THE BOTTOM OF THE YOKE WERE SAWED OFF THE CASTING BY BSA. BOTH TYPES CONTACT THE FORK STOP ON THE FRAME IN THE SAME PLACE - ON THE MAIN BODY OF THE BOTTOM YOKE. WE SUPPOSE THAT THE UPRIGHT POSTS WERE AN ADDITIONAL MEASURE TO MAKE THE FORK STOP MORE ROBUST FOR THE DIRT BIKE ORIENTED FORKS. DON T KNOW WHY BSA DECIDED THEY NEEDED TO SAW THE POSTS OFF? IF TRULY USED OFF ROAD WHERE LAYING THE BIKE DOWN IS A POSSIBILITY, ALL OF THE BSA MODELS NEED TO HAVE THE FORK STOP ON THE FRAME BEEFED UP AND INCREASED IN SURFACE AREA WHERE THE BOTTOM YOKE HITS IT. THIS IS TRUE FROM C15s UP TO THE B50s.

title: Auto Advance Unit 12 Degree 6c
desc: AUTO ADVANCE UNIT 12 DEGREE, 6CA type, NOS LUCAS, AKA 19-1853, This cam can be used in place of 54419653 15 degrees, Given that the timing is set at the full advance position the engine would run fine at the top end. Some unit single enthusiasts feel the 12 degree AAU is an improvement over the 15 degree AAU. This is specially true if you time 28 degrees full advance BTDC as suggested for the earlier Victors, as the 15 degree cam actually retards to 2 degrees past TDC. You may have to slow down the idle on the carb but it certainly won t harm and may even accelerate better. If you want to increase the retard to 15 degrees:, A 12 degree AAU has about 0.134 inches movement for 12 degrees. Therefore you need to go to a total of 0.167 (add 0.033) for the pin movement to get 15 degrees. A Dremel tool with a burr should do the job.

title: Out Front! British Motorcycle
desc: Out FRONT! British Motocross Champions 1960-1974, Author: Ian Berry, Format: Paperback, 272 pages, Publisher: Panther Publishing, Year: 2011, 200 period photos, ISBN: 9780956497536, Price: $ 34.95, A wonderful celebration of some of the best off-road racers there have ever been. The photos alone make Out FRONT! a must have and include many which have never before been published: all are simply stunning. For the BSA unit single enthusiast three of the featured champions are Jeff Smith, Arthur Lampkin, and John Banks all factory BSA campaigners.

title: Bsa Singles Restoration
desc: BSA Singles Restoration, Author: Roy Bacon, Format: Paperback, 304 Pages, Publisher: Andover Norton International, Year: 2012, first published in 1994, 250 illustrations and photos, ISBN: 9780957066526, Price: $49.95,

title: Essential Buyers Guide Bsa Uni
desc: THE ESSENTIAL BUYERS GUIDE, BSA 350, 441 & 500 SINGLES, UNIT CONSTRUCTION SINGLES C15, B25, C25, B40, B44 & B50, 1958-1973, Format: Paperback, 64 Pages, Publisher: Veloce Publishing, Series: Essential Buyer s Guide, Year: 2015, Illustrations: 103 illustrations, Size: 5 x 8, ISBN: 9781845847562, List Price: $18.95, The BSA unit singles - 250, 350, 441 and finally 500cc - may not have been the most glamorous product of the British motorcycle industry, but they were the first bikes for thousands of learner riders and had a great track record in scrambling and motocross. Today, they offer a simple and affordable entry into the world of British classic machines, with a whole range of sizes. Spares are still available, as is friendly and knowledgeable fellow owners. Following the tried-and-tested Veloce Essential Buyer s Guide format, this book delves into what it s like to live with one of these bikes, and the values, advantages and disadvantages of the different models. Plus, of course, what you need to look for when buying one - the engine, transmission, frame, brakes, suspension, paint, chrome and everything else!

title: Bsa Singles Gold Portfolio 194
desc: BSA Singles Gold Portfolio 1945-1963, Author: R.M. Clarke, Format: Paperback, 192 Pages, Publisher: Brooklands Books, Series: Gold Portfolio, ISBN: 9781855204416, Price: $32.95,

title: Bsa Singles Gold Portfolio 196
desc: BSA Singles Gold Portfolio 1964-1974, Author: R.M. Clarke, Format: Paperback, 172 Pages, Publisher: Brooklands Books, Series: Gold Portfolio, ISBN: 9781855204423, Price: $32.95,

title: Bsa Unit Singles
desc: BSA Unit Singles, The Complete Story Including the Triumph Derivatives, Format: Hardcover, 200 Pages, Publisher: Crowood, Year: 2006, 256 illustrations and photos, ISBN: 9781861268433, Price: $34.95,

title: Bsa Gold Star & Other Singles
desc: BSA Gold Star & Other Singles, Author: Roy Bacon, Format: Hardback, 192 Pages, Publisher: Andover Norton International, Year: 2012, first published in 1982, 153 illustrations and photos, ISBN: 9781903088371, Price: $59.95,

title: Rupert Ratio Vol 1, Unit Singl
desc: RUPERT RATIO UNIT SINGLE MANUAL VOL 1: The Engine, Author: Rupert Ratio, Format: Paperback, 275 pages, Publisher: Ratio Publishing, Year: 2014, 300 illustrations, ISBN: 9781999823207, Price: $ 37.50, The Rupert Ratio Unit Single Manual Volume 1: The Engine for BSA C15, B25, B44, B50 and Triumph TR25w is the new updated version of the previously published Rupert Ratio Unit Single Engine Manual. After parts manuals, this book is the most important book to own if you are working on a BSA unit single!!, This new edition is identical to the previous book but has an additional section which provides some further information on the Vertical Oil Pumps, Low Oil Pressure, B50 Oiling, C15 and B40 Steel Flywheels, Wide Ratio Gears; C15/B40 Distributor Engine Inner Timing Cover 1959 to 1964, Clutch Centre Base Plate, B25 Tuning Tips, and Tuning Tips to make the umble ceefer fly. Armed with this book even the least experienced spanner man will be able to not only rebuild a BSA Unit Single, but make it go better and more reliably than even BSA thought possible! This book quite literally takes the BSA (and Triumph) Unit Single engine apart, then it shows how to rebuild the engine correctly. The book includes wiring diagrams, complete specifications, hundreds of illustrations, a wealth of invaluable advice and tuning tips to make your unit single perform!, The Rupert Ratio Unit Single Manual Volume 1: The Engine will also be of interest to all BSA enthusiasts since it charts the development of one of the last and most successful machines to come out of Small Heath. Long after the factory closed Unit Singles were still a competitive force in trials and motocross riding and many are still used for that purpose today. Rupert Ratio is a long time contributor to the journal of the BSA Owners Club, The Star, on technical matters relating to BSA Motorcycles. He is also one of the many Agony Uncles for members of the club, i.e. a technical consultant who can offer advice and assistance to club members when their beloved Beesas are beset by mechanical afflictions. He carries out the latter role under his real name, Dave Smith, who is a design technology teacher by profession.

title: Rupert Ratio Vol 2, Unit Singl
desc: Rupert Ratio Unit Single Manual, Volume 2, Everything But The Engine for BSA C15, B25, B44, B50 and Triumph TR25W, Format: Paperback, 338 pages, Publisher: Ratio Publishing, Year: 2014, 500 illustrations, including 8 page color section, ISBN: 9781999823214, Price: $ 42.00, The Rupert Ratio Unit Single Manual Volume 2: Everything But The Engine for BSA C15, B25, B44, B50 and Triumph TR25W does exactly what it says: covers every model and every variation, from the beginning to the end of the Unit Single production run. This is the most comprehensive restorers guide to the Unit Single there is - a goldmine of invaluable information and advice for all owners of unit singles - in both BSA and Triumph variations. Here you will find a complete description of every component and system of every BSA Unit Single (C15, B40, B25, B44, B50 and Triumph TR25w) including all the myriad detailed factory modifications, the reasons for the changes, modern equivalents (especially paints) and modifications to improve roadworthiness - if it is a Unit Single then the answers are here!, This is, of course the companion volume to the very well known Rupert Ratio Unit Single Engine Manual,

title: Boyer Micro Power Digital Ign
desc: BOYER MICRO POWER DIGITAL IGNITION - UNIT SINGLES, SIDE POINTS MODELS, The Micro Digital ignition provides almost total control over ignition functions. It offers electronic control of advance and retard functions. Because the Micro Digital features a built in computer, the size of a postage stamp, it can make more than a million ignition decisions per second, to constantly monitor engine speed and time the spark precisely to suit. The programming of this micro processor also gives control over ignition coil energy, starting speed, tickover stabilisation and rev limits! These systems are manufactured using the finest semiconductors and are fully encapsulated to protect against moisture intrusion. All units are guaranteed for five years. The Micro-Digital system is must use the supplied Micro Power Coil. The miniature digital ignition coils have a very low primary resistance and a very high quality iron core. title: Valve Spring Set, Beehive, B50
desc: VALVE SPRING SET, BEEHIVE, B50, MADE SPECIALLY FOR BSA UNIT SINGLES LLC BY R/D SPRINGS, COMES WITH TWO SPRINGS AND TOP AND BOTTOM CHROME MOLLY RETAINERS, THE BEEHIVE SPRING IS A SINGLE SPRING WHERE THE DIAMETER OF EACH COIL OF THE SPRING CHANGES SOMEWHAT, FROM NARROWER TO WIDER AT THE MIDDLE TO EVEN NARROWER AT THE TOP.THE MAGIC OF THE BEEHIVE SPRING IS THAT EACH COIL HAS A DIFFERENT RESIDENT FREQUENCY SO THE DIFFERENT FREQUENCIES CANCEL EACH OTHER OUT THUS ALLOWING THE SPRING NOT TO LOOSE CONTROL OF THE VALVE AT HIGH REVS. THESE SPRINGS CAN ALLOW UP TO 300 TO 400 MORE RPMS THAN STANDARD DUAL SPRING SETUPS. STUDIES HAVE ALSO SHOWN THAT BEEHIVE SPRINGS HAVE A MUCH LONGER LIFE THAN REGULAR SPRINGS BEFORE NEEDING REPLACEMENT, ESPECIALLY IN COMPETITION USE. ONE SPRING IS ALSO LIGHTER THAN TWO SPRING SETUPS.WHAT THIS MEANS IS THAT THERE IS NO DOWNSIDE IN USING BEHIVE SPRINGS OTHER THAN A HIGHER INITIAL PURCHASE PRICE OF A SET, THE SEAT PRESSURE AT THE RECOMENDED STATIC SET UP HEIGHT IS 100 LBS. AT FULL LIFT THE SEAT PRESSURE IS AROUND 262 LBS, INSTALATION INSTRUCTIONS COME WITH EACH SET, THIS KIT ONLY WORKS WITH STANDARD DIAMETER B50 VALVE STEMS.NOTE: THE BOTTOM RETAINER REQUIRES THAT THE HEAD AROUND THE VALVE STEM BE MILLED FLAT AS IT IS SLIGHTLY CONCAVE IN THIS LOCATION
